body:
Captain Marvel review

Ok, HOLY SHIT! literally my thought throughout the movie. BUT before we go to that, let’s go to the opening credits where they show the Marvel logo (THE FUCKING OPENING CREDITS) and give the greatest tribute of all time— Stan “THE MAN” Lee. bEST MARVEL OPENING EVER! HANDS DOWN PERIODT. now onto the movie. The movie kicks off naturally and shows the marvelous—hehe, marvelous,—world of the Kree. and then proceeds next to what the sole purpose of the movie is—Kree, Kree, Kree. Long Live The Kree. yeah, bullshit and stuff. but the real deal was Carol Danvers on her journey alone. yeah, sure some moments were a bit off for a moment but it doesn’t take away the joy of Carol exploring while joking around (BRIE LARSON HAS HUMOR YA’LL. SHE CAN ACT.) the biggest part of the movie was when Carol and Nick met and folks … everything is history. need i say more? well, yeah but their tandem. IS. FUCKING. AWESOME. the next sequence is pretty obvious, tbh, when u get to the first half of the movie, unlike previous films that has this sense of mystery, but who cares? CAPTAIN MARVEL WAS ONE FUN-FLICK OF A ROLLER COASTER RIDE. i loved it. the plot may be a bit yada-yada but the main purpose of this is to showcase Carol’s powers. and BOY IT DID NOT DISAPPOINT. it took its time to show how powerful she is and what she’s capable of, which i’m hoping to see more in endgame. ENDGAME. That midcredit scene says everything and I CANT FUCKING WAIT.
